ery是John de St Valéry的女儿，出生在英国英格兰賀福爾蕾托 布藍普頓。她于1129年与Brian de Brampton在英国史洛普爾蕾托 布藍普頓结婚。他们至少是2个儿子和1个女儿的父母。她去世于1157年在英国。"},"hr":{"–1157":"–1157.","1098–1193":"1098–1193","1116–1185":"1116–1185","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1137–Male":"1137–preminuo","1065–1099":"1065–1099.","1099":"1099.","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1185":"1185","1096":"1096","1193":"1193","1129":"1129.","abt 1137":"oko 1137.","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1137":"1137","1136":"1136","1157":"1157.","1179":"1179","about 1116":"oko 1116.","about 1136":"oko 1136.","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","England":"England","Brampton, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Brampton, Herefordshire, England":"Little Brampton, Herefordshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Kinlet, Shropshire, England":"Kinlet, Shropshire, England"},"cs":{"–1157":"–1157","1098–1193":"1098–1193","1116–1185":"1116–1185","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1137–Male":"1137–Zesnulý","1065–1099":"1065–1099","1099":"1099","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1185":"1185","1096":"1096","1193":"1193","1129":"1129","abt 1137":"okolo 1137","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1137":"1137","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1179":"1179","about 1116":"okolo 1116","about 1136":"okolo 1136","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Anglie","England":"Anglie","Brampton, Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie","Brampton, Herefordshire, England":"Little Brampton, Herefordshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, Anglie","Kinlet, Shropshire, England":"Kinlet, Shropshire, Anglie"},"da":{"–1157":"–1157","1098–1193":"1098–1193","1116–1185":"1116–1185","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1137–Male":"1137–Afdød","1065–1099":"1065–1099","1099":"1099","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1185":"1185","1096":"1096","1193":"1193","1129":"1129","abt 1137":"omkring 1137","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1137":"1137","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1179":"1179","about 1116":"omkring 1116","about 1136":"omkring 1136","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","England":"England","Brampton, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Brampton, Herefordshire, England":"Little Brampton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Kinlet, Shropshire, England":"Kinlet, Shropshire, England"},"nl":{"–1157":"–1157","1098–1193":"1098–1193","1116–1185":"1116–1185","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1137–Male":"1137–Overleden","1065–1099":"1065–1099","1099":"1099","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1185":"1185","1096":"1096","1193":"1193","1129":"1129","abt 1137":"circa 1137","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1137":"1137","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1179":"1179","about 1116":"circa 1116","about 1136":"circa 1136","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","England":"England","Brampton, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Brampton, Herefordshire, England":"Little Brampton, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Kinlet, Shropshire, England":"Kinlet, Shropshire, England"},"en":{"–1157":"–1157","1098–1193":"1098–1193","1116–1185":"1116–1185","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1137–Male":"1137–Deceased","1065–1099":"1065–1099","1099":"1099","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1185":"1185","1096":"1096","1193":"1193","1129":"1129","abt 1137":"about 1137","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1137":"1137","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1179":"1179","about 1116":"about 1116","about 1136":"about 1136","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","England":"England","Brampton, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Brampton, Herefordshire, England":"Little Brampton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Kinlet, Shropshire, England":"Kinlet, Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"St","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized spelling of French   St  .   Denis  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Denis","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Camille, Jacques, Armand, Marcel, Andre, Pierre, Serge, Yvan, Alphonse, Edouard, Francois, Gaetane.  Spanish Jose, Carlos, Jorge, Roberto, Angel, Francisco, Joaquin, Juan, Manuel, Miguel, Ramon, Rolando.","French, Walloon, Breton, West Indian (mainly Haiti), German, Dutch, English, and Portuguese; Spanish and Galician (<b>Denís</b>): from the personal name <i>Denis</i>, Spanish and Galician <i>Denís</i>, from Latin <i>Dionysius</i> ‘(follower) of Dionysos’ (see   Dennis  ). Compare   Dennee  .","Ukrainian and Rusyn: variant transliteration of   Denys  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Valery","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Colette, Pierre, Raoul, Yva.","French and West Indian (mainly Haiti): from the personal name <i>Valery</i>, French form of Latin <i>Valerius</i> (see   Valerio  ).","Americanized form of Italian   Valerio   or   Valeri  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vallery","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Leonce, Monique.","French:","habitational name from Vallery in Yonne, once a Gallo-Roman estate, recorded in 1218 as <i>Valerianus</i>."]},{"name":"Valerio","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Ana, Manuel, Pedro, Mario, Luis, Francisco, Ramon, Ruben, Carlos, Jesus.  Italian Antonio, Angelo, Lucio, Francesco, Maurizio, Niccolo, Romeo, Vito, Amadeo, Anastasio, Aureliano, Carmela.","Spanish and Italian: from the personal name <i>Valerio</i>, from Latin <i>Valerius</i>, a Roman surname ultimately derived from Latin <i>valere</i> ‘to flourish, to be strong and healthy’. The name was borne by several early Christian saints, among them 4th-century bishops of Trier and Zaragoza and 5th-century bishops of Sorrento and of Antibes. Compare   Valery  ."]}]},{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":27,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705183,"age":47,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705184,"age":57,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705185,"age":67,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda St Valery was born in Little Brampton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of John de St Valéry. She married Brian de Brampton in 1129, in Little Brampton, Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1157, in England."},"et":{"–1157":"–1157","1098–1193":"1098–1193","1116–1185":"1116–1185","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1137–Male":"1137–Surnud","1065–1099":"1065–1099","1099":"1099","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1185":"1185","1096":"1096","1193":"1193","1129":"1129","abt 1137":"umbes 1137","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1137":"1137","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1179":"1179","about 1116":"umbes 1116","about